This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction. Additionally, the use of bidirectional recurrent neural networks and attention mechanisms are common techniques in this field. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the proposed method involves the use of deep neural networks and multi-instance learning. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the development of a novel attention mechanism for improving the performance of a specific AI task. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks for relation extraction. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the selection of valid instances for predicting relationships between entities, which is a common task in information retrieval.
